'''''5 Minute Dharma''''' is an English-language [[podcast]] that seeks to give people practical [[Buddhist]] wisdom for everyday life. The podcast released a 5-minute episode once per week on Fridays. It is hosted by Dr. Jay N. Forrest.

==Host==
Forrest hosts and produces the show. He studied [[Buddhism]] for over 14 years, both through self-study and through classes, and has been formally trained in [[Zen]] and [[Vipassana]] meditation practices.<ref>{{cite web|title=Buddhist Teachers|url=http://lifeofmindfulness.com/buddhist-teachers/|accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref> Forrest's background and education is in [[Christianity]]. He holds a Doctorate of Ministry degree and, until becoming a Buddhist, had spent 23 years in Christian ministry as a church pastor in Wisconsin, Missouri, Tennessee, Arizona, and New Mexico.<ref>{{cite web|title=Curriculum Vitae|url=http://www.jayforrest.org/p/education-d.html|accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref>

==History==
The ''5 Minute Dharma'' podcast launched on 3 December 2012. The show was the first exclusively Buddhist podcast on [[IHeartRadio Talk|iHeart Radio Talk]].<ref>{{cite web|title=First Buddhist Podcast on iHeart Radio|url=https://www.prlog.org/12249763-first-buddhist-podcast-on-iheart-radio.html | date=30 November 2013 | publisher=PRLog | accessdate=1 May 2019}}</ref> {{As of|2014|February}}, the podcast has had over 100,000 downloads.<ref>{{cite web|title=5 Minute Dharma 100,000 Downloads|url=https://www.prlog.org/12288185-5-minute-dharma-100000-downloads.html|date=26 February 2014|publisher=PRLog|accessdate=1 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Spirituality and Religion Podcasts|url=http://www.stitcher.com/stitcher-list/spirituality-and-religion-podcasts-top-shows|accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref>

==Format==
The podcast is designed to be a simple, non-scholarly introduction to Buddhism. Technical words are kept to a minimum, and when used are explained in [[plain English]]. The podcast is in the style of Dharma talks, which tend to be more conversational and friendly.

